body_html:
@daj Thanks for answer,

However I did it. I has check ops_to_register.h file and it contained Identity function.

So after I rebuilt it and load on Android Studio that error happened:
org.tensorflow.TensorFlowException: Op type not registered 'Identity' in binary running on localhost. Make sure the Op and Kernel are registered in the binary running in this process.

Is there any other error that I could have made or probably the error is in the libtensorflow_inference.so build?

body:
@daj Thanks for answer,

However I did it. I has check `ops_to_register.h` file and it contained `Identity` function. 

So after I rebuilt it and load on Android Studio that error happened: 
`org.tensorflow.TensorFlowException: Op type not registered 'Identity' in binary running on localhost. Make sure the Op and Kernel are registered in the binary running in this process.`

Is there any other error that I could have made or probably the error is in the `libtensorflow_inference.so` build?
